The article is a tribute to Ellen Casey, whom the author greatly admired. They describe Ellen as someone who embodied the values of honesty, decency, integrity, and character. Kindness was seen as a sign of strength, and hard work and family were highly valued. Ellen, along with her husband Bob, raised their eight children with these values and instilled in them a devotion to family and serving others. The author also highlights Ellen's support for her husband during his time as Pennsylvania's governor and her work in literacy and breast cancer. They express their admiration for Ellen's son, Bobby, who has become a respected member of the United States Senate. The author concludes by expressing their gratitude to Ellen and Bob for their legacy and sends their condolences to the Casey family.